description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to support communications with one of the largest and most engaged workforces in the NHS?This is a fantastic opportunity to join the award-winning communications team at Guy’s and St Thomas’ NHS Foundation Trust and help us shape how we involve, inform and inspire our staff so that they can deliver the best possible patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Senior Internal Communications Officer, you will be a trusted advisor on all things internal communications, supporting our clinical and corporate teams to deliver clear and timely information to our staff. You will play a vital part in enabling us to deliver a wide-range of different communications activity, from all-staff briefings and priority operational messages to targeted campaigns and awareness days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work very closely with directors and senior managers across the Trust to make sure that organisational priorities are being communicated using the most effective and efficient methods and channels. You will also be a champion for our staff, ensuring that their voices are heard and that we make best use of their knowledge, expertise and views in developing our communications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an organisation we never stand still, and this applies equally to our communications team. We are looking for someone who is always looking to identify opportunities for new and better ways of doing things.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a superb writer, a creative thinker, calm under pressure and just as comfortable developing a communications plan as delivering it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of a large and busy communications team, you will have the opportunity to be involved in a wide range of high-profile work which, in the last year alone, has involved responding to the unprecedented COVID-19 pandemic, facilitating VIP visits and supporting fundraising initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Currently members of the team are working on a rota basis so there is an expectation that you will work on site, and work from home on some days – this will be kept under review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameScott ThorntonJob titleSenior Internal Communications ManagerEmail addressscott.thornton@gstt.nhs.ukTelephone number020 7188 1551&lt;/p&gt;
